  {
    "index": 3,
    "hash": "W1CVxpB2fzA3UFLyzN2+wpeAIww=",
    "timestampUtcMs": "2026-05-13T13:00:35.000Z",
    "action": {
      "type": "SET_CONTENT",
      "input": {
        "content": "# getUserSelectionPriceBreakdown is the core pricing calculation engine\n\nLocated at `document-models/service-offering/src/utils.ts`, this is the most important business logic function in the project.\n\n## Signature\n\n```typescript\nfunction getUserSelectionPriceBreakdown(\n  state: ServiceOfferingPHState,\n  selection: UserSelection\n): PriceBreakdown\n```\n\n## What It Computes\n\nGiven a ServiceOffering state and a user's selection (tier, billing cycle, enabled add-ons, per-group overrides):\n\n1. **Tier base price** \u2014 Sum of regular groups' monthly prices \u00d7 billing cycle months\n2. **Regular group breakdowns** \u2014 Per-group recurring amounts with discounts, setup costs\n3. **Setup group breakdowns** \u2014 Setup-only groups (no recurring, setup cost only)\n4. **Add-on breakdowns** \u2014 Selected add-on pricing with independent billing cycles\n5. **Totals** \u2014 Grand recurring total, grand setup total, add-on totals\n\n## Internal Helpers\n\n- `applyDiscount()` \u2014 Applies percentage or flat amount discounts\n- `buildResolvedDiscount()` \u2014 Creates discount result with original/discounted amounts\n- `getGroupPriceForTier()` \u2014 Gets monthly price for group-tier pair (tier-dependent \u2192 standalone fallback)\n- `getGroupIndependentDiscount()` \u2014 Extracts tier-dependent pricing discounts\n- `resolveGroupDiscountForTier()` \u2014 Resolves discount checking billingCycleDiscounts then tier-dependent\n- `computeRegularGroupBreakdown()` \u2014 Full breakdown for recurring groups\n- `computeSetupGroupBreakdown()` \u2014 Full breakdown for setup-only groups\n- `computeAddOnBreakdown()` \u2014 Full breakdown for add-on groups\n\n## Used By\n\n- `TheMatrix.tsx` in the service-offering editor \u2014 the pricing configuration panel\n\nSince [[service-offering model defines tiered pricing with option groups and service groups]], this function resolves all the pricing relationships into concrete numbers.\n\n---\n\nTopics:\n- [[helper functions]]\n- [[model-editor wiring]]",
        "updatedAt": "2026-05-13T13:00:35.000Z"
      },
      "timestampUtcMs": "2026-05-13T13:00:35.000Z"
    }
  },
